-- Booz & Co. Picks Mainardi as Chief Executive to Succeed Banerji
-- B y   L e e   S p e a r s
-- 2012-02-12T21:35:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-12/booz-co-picks-mainardi-as-chief-executive-to-succeed-banerji.html
Booz & Co.’s board elected Cesare
Mainardi as chief executive officer to succeed Shumeet Banerji,
the company said today in a statement.  Mainardi, currently the firm’s chief operating officer and
managing director of its North American business, will take on
the new role by mid-May, Booz said. Banerji is nearing
completion of a four-year term as CEO, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lee Spears in New York at 
 lspears3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
